{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}} The '''ACM Symposium on User Interface Software and Technology''' ('''UIST''') is an annual conference for technical innovations in [[human–computer interaction|human–computer interfaces]]. UIST is sponsored by [[ACM SIGCHI]] and [[ACM SIGGRAPH]]. By impact factor, it is the most impactful conference in the field of human–computer interaction.<ref>http://arnetminer.org/page/conference-rank/html/HCI.html</ref><ref>http://oulasvirta.posterous.com/81433178</ref> [[Scott Hudson (computer scientist)|Scott Hudson]] is the current chair of the [http://www.sigchi.org/communities/uist UIST community], which organizes the UIST conference.
UIST 2014 was held in [[Honolulu]], [[Hawaii]], USA, 5–8 October 2014. UIST 2015 will be held in [[Charlotte, NC]] USA, 8–11 November 2015.
== Overview == UIST is a highly selective conference, with an acceptance rate of 20.3% over the last five years.<ref>http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=2380116</ref>
== History == {{expand section|date=March 2013}}
<ref>http://www.acm.org/uist/archive/</ref> Through 2013, UIST was well known for its intimate single-track format. UIST 2014 introduced a new dual-track format.
