[[Image:Kakul Passingoutprade Oweis.JPG|thumb|A passing out parade at [[Pakistan Military Academy]], Kakul.]]

'''Passing out''' is the completion of a course by military or other service personnel or the graduation from a college.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Extraordinary-security-arrangements-for-IMA-passing-out-parade/Article1-357590.aspx |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130125144758/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Extraordinary-security-arrangements-for-IMA-passing-out-parade/Article1-357590.aspx |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2013-01-25 |title=Extraordinary security arrangements for IMA passing out parade |publisher=Hindustan Times |date=2008-12-12 |accessdate=2013-08-01 }}</ref> [[Soldier]]s sometimes take part in a passing out [[Military parade|parade]] upon completion of a [[basic training]] course.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://iprep.ns.sg/passing-out-parade.html |title=iPrepNS &#124; Passing out parade |publisher=Iprep.ns.sg |date= |accessdate=2013-08-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714181809/http://iprep.ns.sg/passing-out-parade.html |archivedate=2014-07-14 |df= }}</ref>

The parade may also be referred to as a 'Marching out' parade as it is at the [[Army Recruit Training Centre]] at [[Kapooka]] in Australia.<ref name=ozarmy-marchout>{{cite web|title=March Out parade information|url=http://www.army.gov.au/Army-life/Army-careers/ARTC-Kapooka/Soldier-Training/March-Out-Parade-Information|publisher=Australian Army|accessdate=2015-02-18}}</ref>

